str2: To deceive thoroughly. From ek and apatao; to seduce wholly.

str2: If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of a primary verb, doko dok'-o of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem.
I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Wise, learned, cultivated, skilled, clever. Akin to saphes; wise.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
From the same as aei; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity; by implication, the world; specially a Messianic period.

str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Probably from the base of musterion; dull or stupid, i.e. Heedless, blockhead, absurd.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
